---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  pageType="guide"
  guideTopic="delivery"
  title="Shipping Container Delivery Requirements | Steel Box Direct"
  description="Learn how shipping container delivery works, site requirements, access needs, and how to prepare your property."
>
  <div class="guide-header guide_header" style="background: var(--c3-deliver); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sh guide_eyebrow" style="border-color: var(--cream);">
        <span class="idx">§ 03</span>
        <span class="nm" style="color: var(--cream);">Decision: Delivery</span>
        <span class="tg" style="color: var(--cream);">Logistics Standards</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="big guide_headline" style="color: var(--cream);">Will it even<br><em>Get there?</em></h1>
      <p class="guide-lede guide_lede" style="opacity: .9;">
        Narrow lanes, soft ground, low branches — we plan for it. Most rural properties can receive a container,
        but you need to know the clearance requirements before you buy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="guide-content guide_content">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="row guide_main_row">
        <div class="main-col guide_main_col">
          <h2>How Containers Are Delivered</h2>
          <p>The delivery method depends on your property access. A 65-foot truck combination needs room to maneuver.</p>

          <div class="method-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--c3-deliver);">
            <h3>Tilt-Bed Truck</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--c3-deliver); margin-bottom: 12px;">The Farm Standard</div>
            <p>The truck tilts its bed and slides the container off onto the ground. Requires 100+ feet of straight approach.</p>
            <div class="who guide_comparison_item_tag">→ Best for clear driveways</div>
          </div>

          <div class="method-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--c2-cond);">
            <h3>Crane-Set</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--c2-cond); margin-bottom: 12px;">Tight Access Solution</div>
            <p>A separate crane lifts the container into place. Solves sharp turns, fencelines, or soft ground issues.</p>
            <div class="who guide_comparison_item_tag" style="background: var(--c2-cond); color: var(--cream);">→ Mike · rural access</div>
          </div>

          <div class="guide_section">
            <h3>The Quick Clearance Checklist</h3>
            <ul class="check-list guide_section_body">
              <li><strong>Width:</strong> 12 feet minimum clearance.</li>
              <li><strong>Height:</strong> 14 feet overhead (branches/wires).</li>
              <li><strong>Ground:</strong> Must support a 30,000 lb truck.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar-col guide_sidebar_col">
          <div class="authority-card guide_callout">
            <div class="m guide_callout_label">Logistics Data</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>92%</strong> of rural properties can receive tilt-bed delivery.</li>
              <li><strong>60 feet</strong> is the average truck length.</li>
              <li><strong>95%</strong> of access issues are solved by crane-set.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="cta-card guide_cta">
            <h4 class="guide_cta_headline">Not sure?</h4>
            <p>Send us a photo of your driveway with your quote request.</p>
            <a href="/quote/" class="btn guide_cta_btn">Check My Access <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .guide-header {
      padding: 80px 0 64px;
      border-bottom: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .guide-lede {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      margin: 40px 0 0;
      max-width: 720px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .guide-content {
      padding: 96px 0;
      background: var(--cream);
    }

    .row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
      gap: 80px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .method-card {
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      border-left: 8px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink);
    }
    .method-card h3 {
      font-family: var(--narrow);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 28px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .who {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: .08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 4px 8px;
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .check-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 40px 0 0;
    }
    .check-list li {
      padding: 16px 0;
      border-bottom: 1.5px solid rgba(11,15,26,.1);
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    .check-list li::before {
      content: "→";
      color: var(--c3-deliver);
      margin-right: 12px;
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .authority-card {
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      padding: 32px;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .authority-card .m { color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .authority-card li { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.45; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(246,241,231,.1); padding-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card li:last-child { border: none; }

    .cta-card {
      margin-top: 40px;
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--c3-deliver);
    }
    .cta-card h4 { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .cta-card p { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .guide-header { padding: 48px 0; }
      .big { font-size: clamp(48px, 10vw, 80px); }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>